<HEADLINE> Police Find Five Dead in Va. Home  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- Police checking on a tip that there might
be dead bodies in a suburban Richmond home said Thursday night they
found five bodies in the residence.
</P>
<P>
   Police Chief Carl Baker said a handgun was recovered, but he
would not say whether all the victims were shot. He gave no other
details about what police found inside the home during a short
briefing.
</P>
<P>
   The tip was called in to the Chesterfield County Emergency
Communications Center, said Don Kappel, the county's director of
public affairs. He said some of the victims knew each other, but
the identities and any relations to one another were being withheld
until relatives could be notified.
</P>
<P>
   Neighbors said a woman, two men and two children lived in the
house and had been there for at least three years.
</P>
</TEXT>
