<HEADLINE> Ex-girlfriend testifies in Columbia University student murder  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - A former girlfriend of Edmund Ko testified in
his murder trial that he restrained her on a barren New Jersey road
while his girlfriend viciously slashed her face, scalp and legs in
a jealous rage.
</P>
<P>
   Diane Kim, 26, testified in State Supreme Court in Manhattan on
Thursday that Ko, 26, held her arms while Claudia Seong, 34,
slashed her scalp so deeply that the knife entered her skull.
Seong's younger sister, Young Joo Seong, sat on her knees to pin
her down, Kim said. The Seongs have been charged in the attack and
freed on bail.
</P>
<P>
   The November 1997 attack was four months before another former
girlfriend of Ko's, Hyeseung Lynda Hong, 26, was found dead in her
apartment near Columbia University, where she was a law student.
Ko, of Fort Lee, N.J., is being tried for Hong's murder.
</P>
<P>
   Kim said Ko contacted her in June 1997, shortly after their
two-month relationship ended, and told her she was among the former
girlfriends he was telling not to contact him or acknowledge him in
public because he was in a new relationship. Hong had similarly
been warned, according to court testimony.
</P>
<P>
   Ko did not contact Kim again until the early morning of Nov. 18,
1997, when, after several phone calls, she agreed to meet him at 3
a.m., Kim said. Kim said she was picked up by Ko and the Seongs,
and was driven to a deserted stretch of road.
</P>
<P>
   After Ko pushed and hit her, Kim said, he pushed her backward
over a barricade. Pinned to the ground by Ko and the younger Seong,
Kim said she was then slashed by Claudia Seong, and was left to
walk home covered in blood.
</P>
<P>
   Throughout the trial, testimony has repeatedly focused on the
elder Seong, of Ridgefield Park, N.J., who refused to answer any
questions in her courtroom appearance earlier this month. Both
sides have acknowledged that she is violently jealous. Seong has
not been charged in Hong's slaying.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
