<HEADLINE> Bob Hope Said Recovering Well  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Bob Hope has returned to his Toluca Lake
estate and is doing well a month after emergency hospitalization
for gastrointestinal bleeding, his daughter said.
</P>
<P>
   ''He seems to be enjoying being back in town and is doing
well,'' Linda Hope said Thursday when asked about her 97-year-old
father. Hope spokesman Ward Grant was on vacation and there were no
other details.
</P>
<P>
   Hope and his wife, Dolores, were at their desert home 100 miles
east of Los Angeles on June 1 when he fell ill and was taken to
Eisenhower Medical Center in Rancho Mirage. He was released a week
later.
</P>
<P>
   The Hopes remained in the desert for another week while
renovations were completed on their home in Toluca Lake, a San
Fernando Valley hamlet behind Universal Studios Hollywood.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
