<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-30 08:37 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lynyrd Skynyrd Graves Vandalized  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ORANGE PARK, Fla. (AP) -- The graves of two members of the
Southern rock group Lynyrd Skynyrd have been vandalized, Clay
County authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Police called to Jacksonville Memory Gardens early Thursday
found the damaged graves of Ronnie Van Zant and Steve Gaines, who
were killed when the band's airplane crashed Oct. 20, 1977.
</P>
<P>
   Van Zant's casket was pulled from a tomb to the ground,
sheriff's department spokeswoman Mary Justino said. His remains
were believed to be intact, but Justino said the cremated remains
of Gaines had been spilled and then recovered.
</P>
<P>
   The disturbed remains have been taken to a mortuary while family
members decide what they want to do with them, Justino said.
</P>
<P>
   ''They just couldn't understand why someone would do this,'' she
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
