<HEADLINE> Dow Slips 30; Nasdaq Climbs 16  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down 30
points in today's early going. Advancing issues on the New York
Stock Exchange hold a 9-7 lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 16 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down two points.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts say today's market session is up for grabs.
</P>
<P>
   It is the final session of the second quarter. And because of
that, you could see some last-minute moves by portfolio managers to
dress up their holdings.
</P>
<P>
   At the same time, with many market players expected to take an
extended Independence Day holiday, today's session could simply be
a wash.
</P>
<P>
   It appears there will be little reaction to May figures on
personal income and spending, which came out largely as expected.
</P>
<P>
   Bond prices are edging higher.
</P>
