<HEADLINE> Stocks Mixed at Midafternoon  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mixed Friday, with worries over
corporate earnings and rising interest rates hurting blue-chip
shares while a surge in semiconductor stocks lifted the technology
sector.
</P>
<P>
   In midday trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial
average was down 13.79 at 10,384.25, adding to Thursday's 129-point
drop.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
index was up 4.37 at 1,446.76 and the Nasdaq composite index was up
56.19 at 3,933.42.
</P>
