<HEADLINE> Clinton Establishes Valor Medal  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- A new presidential medal to recognize
extraordinary heroism by the nation's public safety officers was
established Friday by President Clinton.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton signed an executive order creating the ''Presidential
Medal of Valor'' to be awarded each year to up to 10 law
enforcement personnel, firefighters, and emergency service
providers.
</P>
<P>
   The medal will be awarded from a list of federal, state and
local public safety officers recommended by the U.S. attorney
general.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton said the purpose is to recognize those officers found to
have shown ''extraordinary valor above and beyond the call of duty
in the exercise of their official duties.''
</P>
</TEXT>
