<HEADLINE> Gas station attendant murdered and robbed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   BERNARDS TOWNSHIP, N.J. (AP) - An attendant at an isolated gas
station off Interstate 78 was robbed and shot to death as he was
giving directions to a woman and her daughter, Somerset County
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Other customers were at the King George Exxon at 9:20 p.m.
Thursday when Joseph Sass, 31, of Phillipsburg, Warren County, was
shot once in the face, authorities said. He was pronounced dead at
Morristown Memorial Hospital.
</P>
<P>
   The gunman remains at large.
</P>
<P>
   The suspect, described as a black man in his mid-20s, had
approached Sass moments earlier, asking if the vending machines
took dollar bills, Somerset County Prosecutor Wayne J. Forrest
said.
</P>
<P>
   Sass said they did, and the man went to the machines.
</P>
<P>
   The man then returned to Sass, who was giving the motorist
directions, and asked for change of a $5 bill, Forrest said.
</P>
<P>
   Sass took cash from a pocket and began counting five $1 bills
when the man pointed a handgun in his face and demanded all the
money, Forrest said.
</P>
<P>
   Sass complied and was shot once, he said.
</P>
<P>
   The gunman lowered the gun and walked to the nearby access road
for the Warren Township sewage plant. Soon after, a van left the
access road and headed west on Interstate 78, Forrest said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
