<HEADLINE> Vic Damone Delays Farewell Concerts  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- On the advice of doctors, singer Vic Damone
postponed his farewell concert tour and will take the summer off.
</P>
<P>
   Damone, 72, was hospitalized Monday at a New Jersey hospital for
what was then described as flulike symptoms. He was released
Wednesday and returned to his New Jersey home to recuperate from
severe exhaustion and dehydration.
</P>
<P>
   Damone has recorded more than 2,000 songs during his 53-year
career, including ''An Affair To Remember,'' ''On The Street Where
You Live'' and ''You're Breaking My Heart.''
</P>
<P>
   Damone's farewell tour will resume in the fall and end with his
final concert at New York's Carnegie Hall May 18, 2001.
</P>
