<HEADLINE> By The Associated Press  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   The weekend will start out sunny and pleasant, with
clouds
increasing and temperatures rising on Sunday, according to the
National Weather Service.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Saturday will be sunny and breezy with highs in the upper 70s to
low 80s. Lows will range from 55 to 65 under clear to partly cloudy
skies Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Sunday is expected to be mostly sunny in eastern New York, but
there will be more clouds in the north and west with a chance of an
afternoon shower or thunderstorm in the Adirondacks and near
Watertown. Temperatures Sunday are expected to be in the mid 80s.
</P>
<P>
   The extended forecast calls for partly cloudy skies on Monday
and Tuesday with a chance of a shower or thunderstorm and highs in
the low 80s.
