<HEADLINE> Benedetto captures jumping crown  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   LAKE PLACID, N.Y. (AP) - James Benedetto rode Kondor to victory
in the $7,500 Turtle Lane Farm Jump-off Friday at the 31st annual
Lake Placid Horse Show.
</P>
<P>
   Eight of 31 starters qualified for a tiebreaking jump-off by
riding without penalty over the original 14-jump course at the
North Elba Show Grounds. Benedetto, of Northport, rode Kondor to a
second fault-free run through the course in 31.987 seconds.
</P>
<P>
   Laura Kraut of Oconomowoc, Wis., winner of last Sunday's
$100,000 Rolex U.S. Show Jumping Championship at the U.S.
Equestrian Team Olympic Training Center in Gladstone, N. J., was
fourth to try the jump-off course and she beat Benedetto's time,
finishing in 31.813 seconds. Kraut's horse, Anthem, hit a rail on
the second-to-last fence for a penalty of four faults and a
fifth-place finish. Kraut is the top ranked rider for the U.S.
Equestrian Team's Olympic show jumping squad.
</P>
<P>
   Second place went to Jimmy Torano of Fort Lauderdale, Fla., who
had a fault-free ride in 32.616 seconds on Extra. Christopher
Cawley of Keswick, Va., was third with a clean ride in 34.493
seconds on Brave Ally.
</P>
<P>
   The Lake Placid Horse Show runs through Sunday, ending with the
$50,000 Budweiser Grandprix of Lake Placid.
</P>
</TEXT>
