<HEADLINE> Sally Carpenter Hale named COB for New Jersey  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - Sally Carpenter Hale, assistant chief of bureau
for The Associated Press in Philadelphia, has been promoted to
chief of bureau for New Jersey.
</P>
<P>
   The appointment was announced Friday by AP President and CEO
Louis D. Boccardi.
</P>
<P>
   Hale will be based in Trenton and responsible for AP operations
in New Jersey. She succeeds Mark Mittelstadt, who has been named
the AP's director of editorial planning.
</P>
<P>
   Hale, 45, joined the AP in Dallas in 1979 after working as a
copy editor for The Dallas Morning News. She became AP news editor
in Portland, Ore., in 1984, and assistant chief of bureau in
Philadelphia in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Hale grew up in Houston and is a graduate of the University of
Texas at Austin.
</P>
