<HEADLINE> Sixty Killed in Ethiopian Bus Crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ADDIS ABABA, Ethiopia (AP) -- Sixty people were killed when a bus
plunged into a river in central Ethiopia while attempting to cross
a flooded bridge, state radio reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Rescue workers found seven survivors, some of whom were injured
in the accident Thursday morning near Welenchiti, 80 miles east of
the capital, Addis Ababa, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
   Witnesses said the bus overturned several times after plunging
into the river, which had flooded after heavy rains, the radio
reported.
</P>
<P>
   Among the dead were 21 women and four university students, who
graduated this month.
</P>
<P>
   No other details were immediately available.
</P>
</TEXT>
