<HEADLINE> With BC-NJ--Op Sail 2000-NJ  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Here is a look at traffic preparation at Liberty
State Park
during OpSail 2000 on July 4. No vehicular traffic will be allowed
into the park and visitors will have to walk, take a shuttle or
ride the light rail. The New Jersey Turnpike also will have some
closures:
<TEXT>
<P>
   Shuttles: The Department of Transportation has established free
parking at:
</P>
<P>
   - North Bergen Park &AMP; Ride location next to routes 495 and 3.
</P>
<P>
   - Vince Lombardi Park &AMP; Ride on the New Jersey Turnpike near
Interchange 18.
</P>
<P>
   - Military-Ocean Terminal (MOTBY), Bayonne, off Route 169.
</P>
<P>
   NJ Transit will provide service from the MOTBY lot to Liberty
State Park from 8 a.m. until 7 p.m., or until the lot is full.
Return service from the park will be available from 8:30 a.m. until
all passengers have been transported back to the MOTBY lot. Private
carriers will provide free service from the North Bergen and Vince
Lombardi lots.
</P>
<P>
   Rail: The Hudson-Bergen Light Rail will provide service to the
park from Bayonne and Jersey City. No fares will be charged on the
rail after 9 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   New Jersey Turnpike: Exits 14B and 14C will be closed. Officials
may decide to close the Newark Bay/Hudson County Extension if
traffic warrants. Expect congestion at exit 14A.
</P>
<P>
   ---
</P>
<P>
   Source: New Jersey State Police; New Jersey Turnpike Authority.
</P>
