<HEADLINE> 1 Dead, 10 Injured at Rock Festival  </HEADLINE>
At least one dead, 10 injured at rock festival
<TEXT>
<P>
   COPENHAGEN, Denmark (AP) -- At least one person was killed and 10
others injured late Friday during Pearl Jam concert at one of
Europe's largest rock festivals, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Details of the incident were sketchy, but the casualties
occurred while the band was playing at the festival's main Orange
Stage. According to early unconfirmed reports, spectators were
injured when they were apparently crushed by against the stage.
</P>
<P>
   The Norwegian news agency NTB, which had a reporter at the
Roskilde Rock Festival, said there were four dead and 20 injured,
Danish radio also gave those figures, citing festival spokesman
Leif Skov.
</P>
<P>
   Police said they were swamped with calls from worried parents
and could confirm only one death.
</P>
<P>
   Danish radio reported that 10 ambulances were dispatched to the
scene.
</P>
<P>
   The Roskilde festival, first held in 1971, was inspired by the
1969 Woodstock Festival in the United States. It is held annually
on a farm in Roskilde, 25 miles west of the capital, Copenhagen.
</P>
</TEXT>
