<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tex. Co. Recalls Italian Sausages  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- A Texas company is recalling about 8,500
pounds of Italian sausages after a customer called to complain
about finding plastic in the product.
</P>
<P>
   Owens Country Sausage, of Richardson, Texas, produced the meat
on May 3 and distributed it to retail stores in Texas, Louisiana,
Oklahoma, Kansas and Arkansas, the Department of Agriculture's Food
Safety and Inspection Service announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
   The company has not announced any reports of sickness or injury.
</P>
<P>
   The product being recalled is 16-ounce rolls of Owens brand
Italian sausage. Each package label has a code of ''5A3'' or
''5B3,'' a ''Sell-By'' date of June 17, 2000, and ''Est. 403''
appears on the label inside the USDA seal of inspection.
</P>
<P>
   USDA officials urged consumers to check their kitchens for the
product, and return them to the store.
</P>
<P>
   Consumers with questions should call Owens Country Sausage at
972-235-7181.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: USDA Food Safety and Inspection Service:
http://www.fsis.usda.gov/
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
