<HEADLINE> Cowboys Sign Two NFL Europe Players  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas (AP) -- The Dallas Cowboys signed former NFL Europe
defensive back Stephen Fisher and offensive lineman Michael Leis on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Fisher, who played at North Carolina, led the Rhein Fire with
three interceptions last season. He also averaged 23 yards on punt
returns and 24 yards on kickoffs.
</P>
<P>
   Leis, 6-foot-3 and 309 pounds, started at guard for the
Amsterdam Admirals. He played at Kansas.
</P>
