<HEADLINE> Mercury 66, Mystics 57  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP)-- Brandy Reed scored 25 points and the Phoenix
Mercury held the Washington Mystics to eight points in the final 16
minutes in a 66-57 victory Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   Phoenix (9-5) improved to 6-0 overall against Washington, with
Reed scoring eight points during a 12-0 run that gave the Mercury
the lead for good midway through the second half.
</P>
<P>
   The Mercury held Washington (6-7) scoreless for 8:53 during the
run, with Reed capping the streak with a 3-pointer that gave
Phoenix a 53-49 lead. Washington cut it to two once, but never made
it closer than three after that.
</P>
<P>
   Washington, winless in five games against Western Conference
teams, missed 16 of its final 19 shots as Phoenix scored 25 of the
last 33 points.
</P>
<P>
   Jennifer Gillom added 16 points for Phoenix. Nikki McCray led
Washington with 19 points, and Chamique Holdsclaw added 17.
</P>
<P>
   The Mystics started the second half by making five of their
first six shots, taking the 49-41 lead when McCray hit a 3-pointer
with 15:57 left.
</P>
</TEXT>
