<HEADLINE> Rochester officer charged with rape  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) - A Rochester police officer has been
charged with threatening and raping a 21-year-old woman.
</P>
<P>
   Curtis Lee Gainey, 41, was arrested Thursday in Irondequoit
following an investigation that started June 23, Irondequoit Police
Chief Richard Boyan told the Rochester Democrat and Chronicle.
</P>
<P>
   Gainey, a 10-year-veteran, had been on the job until the day he
was arrested. He was arraigned and jailed in lieu of $10,000 bail.
</P>
<P>
   The Rochester Police Department suspended Gainey with pay,
pending the results of an internal affairs investigation and the
criminal investigation.
</P>
<P>
   Boyan said Gainey is accused of raping a 21-year-old woman June
3 in Irondequoit, a suburb of Rochester. The woman did not tell
police about the rape until June 23.
</P>
<P>
   Monroe County District Attorney Howard Relin said Gainey had a
relationship with the woman and said, ''this was not one incident.
It was over a long period of time.''
</P>
