<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-30 23:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suburban Mayor in Murder Plot  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- The mayor of a Miami suburb was convicted Friday of
trying to hire someone to kill her ex-husband.
</P>
<P>
   Gilda Cabrera Oliveros, the suspended mayor of Hialeah Gardens,
sat silently in the courtroom as the jury read its verdict. Her two
daughters sobbed a few rows behind her.
</P>
<P>
   Last fall, investigators looking into charges of possible vote
fraud were told by several former city workers that the mayor had
approached them about killing her then-husband, Angel Ramos.
</P>
<P>
   Former parks director Ricardo Vazquez said at the time that
Oliveros, mayor of the town of 18,000 since 1989, frequently asked
for medicine he took for an injury.
</P>
<P>
   ''Gilda would come here and ask me for my pills,'' he said.
''She'd say, 'I want to kill my husband.'''
</P>
<P>
   Besides two counts of soliciting murder, the mayor was convicted
of three counts of election fraud.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
