<HEADLINE> Police Arrest Expelled Senator  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BRASILIA, Brazil (AP) -- Police arrested former senator Luiz
Estevao on Friday, two days after he was expelled for misconduct
and lost his congressional immunity from prosecution.
</P>
<P>
   Estevao faces more than a dozen charges of financial wrongdoing,
including the embezzlement of nearly $93 million earmarked for the
construction of the yet-unfinished Sao Paulo State Labor Courthouse
by his construction firm.
</P>
<P>
   A wealthy businessman with a personal fortune estimated at $250
million, Estevao gained renown as a financial backer and personal
friend of former President Fernando Collor de Mello, who was
impeached for corruption in 1992.
</P>
