<HEADLINE> Candidate Drops Gun Prizes  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SALLISAW, Okla. (AP) -- A congressional candidate who had planned
to give away guns as prizes at a campaign fund-raiser Friday
decided instead to call off the banquet.
</P>
<P>
   Mark Detro, who is seeking the Republican nomination for the
House seat being vacated by GOP Rep. Tom Coburn, said the Oklahoma
Republican Party had recommended several times that he abandon the
plan.
</P>
<P>
   The attorney general's office had also said the plan was
illegal.
</P>
<P>
   The banquet that was to have been Friday will be rescheduled
later. Detro said it wasn't likely to have anything to do with guns
-- other than his campaign's emphasis on the freedom to bear arms.
</P>
<P>
   ''The Second Amendment is still a big issue with my campaign,
but I didn't want to alienate myself from the Republican Party,''
he said. ''I didn't want to put myself in that predicament.''
</P>
